<br>
I have a question regarding raptors specifically and their speed though.<br>
<br>
Some mobs (ulthork, spirocs, spectors, drakkels), if you know they will all be dead on the next blast (or all but one) and snare drops, you can forego snare on the last blast.. ie get to max range then start casting as they are coming in full bore. This adds a bit of excitement to an otherwise dull process, and its a rush to see 4 mobs drop dead at your feet<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Is this possible with raptors or are they just too fast? I gather they can knock you for a loop, and I'd prefer not to even risk losing the peridot if I didn't need to .. and obviously I don't want to risk dying just to save a little mana and to spice things up.<br>
