<br>
Atol's vs BoF: If you are only doing raptors, not the vics, then BoF is more than adequate. If you are doing any vics you are better off using Atol's. If you are doing Dinus you definitely want to be using Atol's.  <p>Qaman<BR>
Sorcerer<BR>
Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uxarekdawizzie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>XarekdaWizzie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/22/01 12:44:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ok. Quad kite Guru's i seek enlightenment !</span><hr size=1> here are my observations of Atols:<br>
<br>
I used bonds of force lvl 52 - 55.  I FINALLY got atols at lvl 55 and decided to try it.  This is after the fixed the new and improved resistance check.  After using it for a bout 3 hours worth of pulls, I noticed that resists were significantly higher with atols than BoF (id get at least 1 resist every 2 pulls, if not more).  So I switched back to BoF to finish off lvl 55.  when I hit lvl 56, Atol's resists went to almost 0.  1 in 10 pulls would get 1 resist.  For my experiences, use bof til 56, then atol's.  <br>
<br>
Good thing about atol's is it makes the mobs move a LOT slower, and lasts longer, and cast time is really short.  When I solo now, I can do entire large island solo, and dont even use levi/invis to pull any more.  I doubt I could do this with BoF.  <br>
<br>
<br>
Xarek<br>
